to get to Mars, including a massive rocket that'll be able to carry as many as 220,000

07:25.040 --> 07:30.440
pounds to Mars for less than any previous rocket, which could make Martian colonization

07:30.440 --> 07:31.800
economically feasible.

07:31.800 --> 07:37.160
So, after adding everything up, my conservative estimate for one year with four astronauts

07:37.160 --> 07:40.680
on the moon comes out to $36 billion dollars.

07:40.680 --> 07:50.720
That's $98 million per day, $4.1 million per hour, $68,300 per minute, or $1,138 per

07:50.720 --> 07:55.400
second—more than an average family makes in a year in Madagascar.

07:55.400 --> 07:56.760
Is it worth it?

07:56.760 --> 07:57.760
Maybe.

07:57.760 --> 08:01.360
If we ever have to leave earth because of the environmental change that we've started,

08:01.360 --> 08:05.400
that $36 billion dollars might be the best investment we've ever made.

